Edition:
Quote: Fred with an eye torn out when a badly-aimed sprag flew back from the spoke of a downhill truck. 1963 <i>Ibid.</i> 421 [gloss] sprag: A piece of metal or wood inserted between the spokes of the wheel of a moving truck in order to brake it.
